OL,6,F"Jack was supposed to have his
OL,7,Finterview on the day that I held him
OL,8,Fin my arms as he died. Paul got the
OL,9,Fchance to say to a social worker that
OL,10,Fhis dad made him sit at a table and
OL,11,Feat peas until he was sick. Jack never
OL,12,Fgot the chance to say. He had to sit
OL,13,Fat the same table, cry as he watched
OL,14,Fhis brother go through this, and then
OL,15,Fbe called a crybaby by his dad. Their
OL,16,Fvoices were never heard until it was
OL,17,Ftoo late."
OL,19,FMs Throssell still recalls what
OL,20,Fhappened on the day her sons were
OL,21,Fkilled.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
