OL,6,FChief Executive of Women's Aid Farah
OL,7,FNazeer said the "archaic presumption"
OL,8,Fof contact in family court cases has
OL,9,F"put the lives of women and children
OL,10,Fat risk for far too long".
OL,12,F"Contact with an abuser is deeply
OL,13,Fharmful to children, with it not only
OL,14,Frisking their physical and mental
OL,15,Fwellbeing, behaviour, and development,
OL,16,Fbut also their lives, in the most
OL,17,Fextreme of cases.
